comms: So that ends this series. These two sides will again meet in a World Cup warm-up in a few days' time. All this is preparation ahead of the big event. USA as I previously mentioned will be over the moon to grab a series win against a full-member team while Bangladesh would be bitterly disappointed. But still cricket ahead for both these sides before they go into the big event. We close our coverage here of this game. We will be back with more cricket soon. See you and till then don't forget to take care. Bye.
The winning trophy is presented to Monank Patel who accepts it.

B0$ We had a bad game today. We did not assess the conditions as we should have, kudos to Bangladesh for the great win today. It's tough to bat first sometimes here and it comes down to shot selection and we played some poor shots. We are still trying to get the right combination for the World Cup and those two warm-up games are very important for us. We are definitely confident, we have a strong team and we go back to the drawing board, draw up plans, play our best cricket and hopefully we can do well.

B0$ Boys showed a lot of character and everyone executed their plans. It's very disappointing to lose the series, we did not play well to be honest. But to finish on a high today will help us ahead of the World Cup. We know the conditions and how it will be and we are looking forward.
B0$ Very happy with the way I bowled. I tried a lot of variations and mixed it up. Feeling really good for winning these awards.

B0$ What a statement win from Bangladesh. Only that it came in a consolatory way. The series has already been lost and this is just a face-saving win. USA can be saved criticism for this loss as they are on a high. And they made changes to this game to give their reserve players a chance. Bangladesh with Mustafizur set the tone with the ball and the target was chased down without loss by the openers. The real Bangladesh turned up today and that gave USA no chance. The target of 105 was never going to be enough and Tanzid and Sarkar helped themselves to good morale-boosting knocks ahead of the T20 World Cup. While the USA will be over the moon with the series win, Bangladesh will know that they have a lot of work to do ahead of the World Cup. They would be shocked and gutted to lose this series, when in their minds they would have come here thinking this is going to be an easy series. Stay tuned for the presentations...

B0$ This is a pretty tacky wicket to bat on but USA are still significantly under par. Despite getting a solid start and a fruitful powerplay, the innings fell off a cliff when the spinners came into action. Gous gave a fiery start, but USA got barely anything from the rest of their batters. Rishad Hossain was brilliant with his leg spin on a track that was quite helpful, ending with figures of 1/7. There were three maidens in the innings which highlighted how tough it was for batting, and how tight the Bangla bowlers kept things. The star of the show for the visitors was Mustafizur Rahman who ended with career best figures of 6/10. Bangladesh would fancy chasing this down early, back shortly for the second innings...

Hosts USA have shown that they aren’t there to just make up the numbers at the World Cup, with some enterprising performances from Harmeet Singh, Ali Khan and Corey Anderson. They have a golden opportunity to claim a 3-0 win against the Bangla Tigers, rousing the home fans ahead of some big days in the lives of all those American cricketers. We’re not too far away from the toss, stick around…

Since then, Bangladesh have lost a game against Zimbabwe and two games against USA, relinquishing a series in the process. With the series already decided, all that Bangladesh are playing for today is avoiding the ignominy of being whitewashed by an associate nation. They have found the going tough in Houston, as their tepid batting approach has cost them in both games.

B0$  A couple of weeks back, Shakib Al Hasan claimed that Bangladesh won’t adequately prepared for this T20 World Cup because they are playing weaker teams in the lead up. "In Australia (T20 World Cup in 2022) we went after playing against New Zealand and Pakistan and so certainly we went to the World Cup on the back of very good preparation and taking that into consideration this is not ideal,” he was quoted as saying to the media.
